🛠 Task 1 – View Storage
lsblk

Detailed

lsblk -f

Disk usage

df -h

Filesystem type

df -Th
🛠 Task 2 – View Partitions
sudo fdisk -l

or

sudo parted -l
🛠 Task 3 – Create a Partition (Lab VM)

⚠️ Practice only on a virtual machine or an empty test disk. Do not modify partitions on a production system.

sudo fdisk /dev/sdb

Common commands:

n  Create partition

p  Print table

w  Write changes

q  Quit
🛠 Task 4 – Create Filesystem

EXT4

sudo mkfs.ext4 /dev/sdb1

XFS

sudo mkfs.xfs /dev/sdb1

Verify

sudo blkid
🛠 Task 5 – Mount Filesystem

Create mount point

sudo mkdir /data

Mount

sudo mount /dev/sdb1 /data

Verify

df -h

Unmount

sudo umount /data
🛠 Task 6 – Persistent Mount (/etc/fstab)

Find UUID

sudo blkid

Edit:

sudo nano /etc/fstab

Example entry

UUID=xxxxxxxx-xxxx-xxxx-xxxx-xxxxxxxxxxxx /data ext4 defaults 0 2

Test without reboot

sudo mount -a
🛠 Task 7 – LVM Basics

Create Physical Volume

sudo pvcreate /dev/sdb1

Create Volume Group

sudo vgcreate vgdata /dev/sdb1

Create Logical Volume

sudo lvcreate -L 5G -n lvbackup vgdata

View LVM

sudo pvs
sudo vgs
sudo lvs
🛠 Task 8 – Extend Logical Volume

Extend

sudo lvextend -L +2G /dev/vgdata/lvbackup

Resize EXT4

sudo resize2fs /dev/vgdata/lvbackup

Resize XFS

sudo xfs_growfs /data
🛠 Task 9 – Swap

Current swap

swapon --show

Create 2 GB swap file

sudo fallocate -l 2G /swapfile
sudo chmod 600 /swapfile
sudo mkswap /swapfile
sudo swapon /swapfile

Verify

free -h
🛠 Task 10 – Disk Usage

Largest directories

du -sh /*

Largest files

find / -type f -size +500M
